Year: 1. Data is obtained from the GHCN GHCN repository, specifically:
2. Temperatures are in Celsius, precipitation in mm and snowfall/depth in cm.
3. TAVG is a daily average computed at each station; Tavg is the average of TMAX and TMIN.
4. Data is averaged at the daily level across multiple stations.
5. Data is summarized at the monthly or yearly level using different rules depending on the measure:

Month: - TMAX is aggregated by max(); TMIN is aggregated by min().
- TAVG and Tavg are aggregated by average().
- PRCP and SNOW are aggregated by sum().

Year: 6. Decades begin on Jan 1 in calendar years ending in zero.
7. Seasonal decades/year/quarters begin Dec 1 of the previous calendar year.
